# Testing And TDD

TDD is the default discipline for behavior changes.

- Write or update tests before implementation when behavior changes.
- Use tests to define expected behavior and guard against regressions.
- Treat missing or failing tests as part of the work, not follow-up work.

Testing should fit the change:

- unit tests for business logic
- integration tests for DB, GraphQL, queue, and service boundaries
- end-to-end or system checks for critical flows when appropriate

If strict test-first sequencing is not practical, say so explicitly in the handoff or PR description.
